.:: Puzzle 4x3-Level-1-13::.
3 different games are played: domino, backgammon, snooker
The people use 3 different means of transport: bus, car, snowmobile
City: marseilles, liverpool, london
House: craftsman, townhouse, art-deco
1. the art-deco house is the person playing domino##1
2. the person traveling to london is on the left of the craftsman house##1
3. the person playing backgammon is on the left of the person traveling to london##1
4. the person playing snooker is the person driving the car##1
5. the person traveling to london is on the left of the person traveling to marseilles##1
6. the person driving the snowmobile is on the left of the art-deco house##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |       1       |    2    |     3     |
| Game         | backgammon | domino | snooker   |
| Transport           | snowmobile     | bus    | car   |
| City   | liverpool         | london    | marseilles   |
| House         | townhouse       | art-deco | craftsman |

